# Liminal Calendar — chora-node crontab template
#
# Install:
#   crontab -e   (then paste relevant lines, after substituting env values)
#
# These lines drive server-side work that Vercel Hobby cron can't cover
# (cap: once/day). If the project ever migrates to Vercel Pro, consolidate
# them into vercel.json and delete this file.
#
# Required env (export in the user's shell profile or prepend to each line):
#   CRON_SECRET               — shared secret configured in Vercel env
#   CALENDAR_BASE_URL         — e.g. https://calendar.castalia.one
#
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Every 5 minutes: send due email + push reminders (24h / 1h / 15m / start).
# Width of each time window in the route is 10 minutes, so anything >= every
# 10 min risks missing an event that falls between ticks. 5 min is safe.

*/5 * * * * curl -fsS -H "Authorization: Bearer ${CRON_SECRET}" "${CALENDAR_BASE_URL}/api/cron/send-reminders" >/dev/null 2>&1

# --------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Daily 06:07 local: materialize recurring event instances for the next window.
# NOTE: `/api/cron/materialize` is also scheduled in vercel.json at 06:00.
# Only keep one — this line is here as a fallback for when the Vercel cron
# is disabled or the project is moved off Vercel.

# 7 6 * * * curl -fsS -H "Authorization: Bearer ${CRON_SECRET}" "${CALENDAR_BASE_URL}/api/cron/materialize" >/dev/null 2>&1

# --------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Smoke test (manual, not a cron line). Run ad-hoc to confirm the trigger
# is live — look for new rows in notification_log within the last hour:
#   psql $DATABASE_URL -c "select max(sent_at) from notification_log;"
